            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EHow%20beautifully%20this%20principle%20is%20illustrated%20in%20the%20lives%20of%20Joash%20and%20Paul!%20Little%20Joash%2C%20at%20only%20seven%20years%20of%20age%2C%20was%20defenseless%20against%20the%20ruthless%20Queen%20Athaliah.%20%22Joash%20and%20his%20nurse%20remained%20hidden%20in%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20Lord%20for%20six%20years%20while%20Athaliah%20ruled%20over%20the%20land%22%20(2%20Kings%2011%3A3).%20Only%20the%20Lord%20could%20have%20kept%20him%20from%20crying%20at%20the%20wrong%20moment%20or%20being%20seen%20by%20someone%20who%20was%20friendly%20to%20the%20queen.%20Athaliah%20finally%20met%20her%20death%2C%20the%20Lord%20fulfilling%20His%20promise%20to%20destroy%20the%20wicked.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPaul%20faced%20great%20danger%20from%20the%20Jews%20at%20Corinth.%20%22One%20night%20the%20Lord%20spoke%20to%20Paul%20in%20a%20vision%20and%20told%20him%2C%20%E2%80%98Don't%20be%20afraid!%20Speak%20out!%20Don't%20be%20silent!%20For%20I%20am%20with%20you%2C%20and%20no%20one%20will%20harm%20you%20because%20many%20people%20here%20in%20this%20city%20belong%20to%20me'%20%22%20(Acts%2018%3A9-10).%20The%20Jews'%20efforts%20to%20bring%20legal%20action%20against%20Paul%20ended%20in%20their%20being%20thrown%20out%20of%20court%20in%20one%20moment%20of%20time.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESatan%20makes%20you%20think%20the%20end%20is%20here%2C%20the%20worst%20has%20come%2C%20and%20the%20game%20is%20lost.%20Remember%3A%20It's%20not%20over%20until%20it's%20over.%20The%20Lord%20is%20watching%20over%20you!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Kgs.10:32-12:21",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Kings%2010%3A32-12%3A21%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_10_32%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2210%22%20vn%3D%2232%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Death%20of%20Jehu%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E32%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20about%20that%20time%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20began%20to%20cut%20down%20the%20size%20of%20Israel%26%23x2019%3Bs%20territory.%20King%20Hazael%20conquered%20several%20sections%20of%20the%20country%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_10_33%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2210%22%20vn%3D%2233%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E33%3C%2Fspan%3Eeast%20of%20the%20Jordan%20River%2C%20including%20all%20of%20Gilead%2C%20Gad%2C%20Reuben%2C%20and%20Manasseh.%20He%20conquered%20the%20area%20from%20the%20town%20of%20Aroer%20by%20the%20Arnon%20Gorge%20to%20as%20far%20north%20as%20Gilead%20and%20Bashan.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_10_34%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2210%22%20vn%3D%2234%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E34%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20events%20in%20Jehu%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%26%23x2014%3Beverything%20he%20did%20and%20all%20his%20achievements%26%23x2014%3Bare%20recorded%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Book%20of%20the%20History%20of%20the%20Kings%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_10_35%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2210%22%20vn%3D%2235%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E35%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Jehu%20died%2C%20he%20was%20buried%20in%20Samaria.%20Then%20his%20son%20Jehoahaz%20became%20the%20next%20king.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_10_36%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2210%22%20vn%3D%2236%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E36%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20all%2C%20Jehu%20reigned%20over%20Israel%20from%20Samaria%20for%20twenty-eight%20years.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_1%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Kings%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EQueen%20Athaliah%20Rules%20in%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Athaliah%2C%20the%20mother%20of%20King%20Ahaziah%20of%20Judah%2C%20learned%20that%20her%20son%20was%20dead%2C%20she%20began%20to%20destroy%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20royal%20family.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_2%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Ahaziah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20sister%20Jehosheba%2C%20the%20daughter%20of%20King%20Jehoram%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E11%3A2%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EJoram%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Jehoram.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20took%20Ahaziah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20infant%20son%2C%20Joash%2C%20and%20stole%20him%20away%20from%20among%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20children%2C%20who%20were%20about%20to%20be%20killed.%20She%20put%20Joash%20and%20his%20nurse%20in%20a%20bedroom%2C%20and%20they%20hid%20him%20from%20Athaliah%2C%20so%20the%20child%20was%20not%20murdered.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_3%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EJoash%20remained%20hidden%20in%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20for%20six%20years%20while%20Athaliah%20ruled%20over%20the%20land.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_4%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ERevolt%20against%20Athaliah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20the%20seventh%20year%20of%20Athaliah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20reign%2C%20Jehoiada%20the%20priest%20summoned%20the%20commanders%2C%20the%20Carite%20mercenaries%2C%20and%20the%20palace%20guards%20to%20come%20to%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20He%20made%20a%20solemn%20pact%20with%20them%20and%20made%20them%20swear%20an%20oath%20of%20loyalty%20there%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple%3B%20then%20he%20showed%20them%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_5%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EJehoiada%20told%20them%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20what%20you%20must%20do.%20A%20third%20of%20you%20who%20are%20on%20duty%20on%20the%20Sabbath%20are%20to%20guard%20the%20royal%20palace%20itself.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_6%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EAnother%20third%20of%20you%20are%20to%20stand%20guard%20at%20the%20Sur%20Gate.%20And%20the%20final%20third%20must%20stand%20guard%20behind%20the%20palace%20guard.%20These%20three%20groups%20will%20all%20guard%20the%20palace.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_7%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20other%20two%20units%20who%20are%20off%20duty%20on%20the%20Sabbath%20must%20stand%20guard%20for%20the%20king%20at%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_8%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EForm%20a%20bodyguard%20around%20the%20king%20and%20keep%20your%20weapons%20in%20hand.%20Kill%20anyone%20who%20tries%20to%20break%20through.%20Stay%20with%20the%20king%20wherever%20he%20goes.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_9%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20commanders%20did%20everything%20as%20Jehoiada%20the%20priest%20ordered.%20The%20commanders%20took%20charge%20of%20the%20men%20reporting%20for%20duty%20that%20Sabbath%2C%20as%20well%20as%20those%20who%20were%20going%20off%20duty.%20They%20brought%20them%20all%20to%20Jehoiada%20the%20priest%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_10%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20he%20supplied%20them%20with%20the%20spears%20and%20small%20shields%20that%20had%20once%20belonged%20to%20King%20David%20and%20were%20stored%20in%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_11%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20palace%20guards%20stationed%20themselves%20around%20the%20king%2C%20with%20their%20weapons%20ready.%20They%20formed%20a%20line%20from%20the%20south%20side%20of%20the%20Temple%20around%20to%20the%20north%20side%20and%20all%20around%20the%20altar.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_12%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Jehoiada%20brought%20out%20Joash%2C%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20son%2C%20placed%20the%20crown%20on%20his%20head%2C%20and%20presented%20him%20with%20a%20copy%20of%20God%26%23x2019%3Bs%20laws.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E11%3A12%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Ea%20copy%20of%20the%20covenant.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20They%20anointed%20him%20and%20proclaimed%20him%20king%2C%20and%20everyone%20clapped%20their%20hands%20and%20shouted%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BLong%20live%20the%20king!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_13%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Death%20of%20Athaliah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Athaliah%20heard%20the%20noise%20made%20by%20the%20palace%20guards%20and%20the%20people%2C%20she%20hurried%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple%20to%20see%20what%20was%20happening.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_14%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20she%20arrived%2C%20she%20saw%20the%20newly%20crowned%20king%20standing%20in%20his%20place%20of%20authority%20by%20the%20pillar%2C%20as%20was%20the%20custom%20at%20times%20of%20coronation.%20The%20commanders%20and%20trumpeters%20were%20surrounding%20him%2C%20and%20people%20from%20all%20over%20the%20land%20were%20rejoicing%20and%20blowing%20trumpets.%20When%20Athaliah%20saw%20all%20this%2C%20she%20tore%20her%20clothes%20in%20despair%20and%20shouted%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BTreason!%20Treason!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_15%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Jehoiada%20the%20priest%20ordered%20the%20commanders%20who%20were%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20troops%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BTake%20her%20to%20the%20soldiers%20in%20front%20of%20the%20Temple%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E11%3A15%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EBring%20her%20out%20from%20between%20the%20ranks%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3ETake%20her%20out%20of%20the%20Temple%20precincts.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20meaning%20of%20the%20Hebrew%20is%20uncertain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20kill%20anyone%20who%20tries%20to%20rescue%20her.%26%23x201D%3B%20For%20the%20priest%20had%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BShe%20must%20not%20be%20killed%20in%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_16%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20they%20seized%20her%20and%20led%20her%20out%20to%20the%20gate%20where%20horses%20enter%20the%20palace%20grounds%2C%20and%20she%20was%20killed%20there.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_17%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJehoiada%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Religious%20Reforms%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Jehoiada%20made%20a%20covenant%20between%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20the%20king%20and%20the%20people%20that%20they%20would%20be%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20people.%20He%20also%20made%20a%20covenant%20between%20the%20king%20and%20the%20people.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22kgs2_11_18%22%20bk%3D%22kgs2%22%20ch%3D%2211%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20all%20the%20people%20of%20the%20land%20went%20over%20to%20the%20temple%20of%20Baal%20and%20tore%20it%20down.%20They%20demolished%20the%20altars%20and%20smashed%20the%20idols%20to%20pieces%2C%20and%20they%20killed%20Mattan%20the%20priest%20of%20Baal%20in%20front%20of%20the%20altars.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%2